<h3 local-id=3D"fbac6ac956b0" id=3D"id-=F0=9F=9A=80BMADAcademy=E2=80=94Your=
GuidetoBuildingSmarter-TheGoldenRule=F0=9F=A5=87">The Golden Rule =F0=9F=A5=
=87</h3>
<blockquote local-id=3D"2b0d971b-6b48-4669-8e3f-bee89d70765f">
<p local-id=3D"e2d8ac491c94"><strong>Nothing =E2=80=94 and we mean NOTHING =
=E2=80=94 goes to production without UAT sign-off from Product.</strong></p=
>
</blockquote>
<p local-id=3D"549634ba0536"><strong>Rob</strong> is the keeper of the rele=
ase. He's the one who gets sign-off and pushes to prod. If you're not Rob, =
you don't release to prod. If you are Rob =E2=80=94 no pressure. =F0=9F=98=
=85</p>
<hr local-id=3D"aeb9fecc-7a7d-4458-9249-95170e93de9d">
<h2 local-id=3D"19f8e1523910" id=3D"id-=F0=9F=9A=80BMADAcademy=E2=80=94Your=
GuidetoBuildingSmarter-=F0=9F=9A=ABWhatBMADisNOT">=F0=9F=9A=AB What BMAD is=
 NOT</h2>
<p local-id=3D"f2e9d96ff0ea">Let's bust some myths before they become bad h=
abits:</p>
<p local-id=3D"9fb1aee3db0b">=E2=9D=8C <strong>"BMAD will just do everythin=
g for me"</strong> Nope! Agents produce great drafts. YOU make the final ca=
ll. Always. The human is always in the loop.</p>
<p local-id=3D"60cc1f0745cc">=E2=9D=8C <strong>"I can just auto-deploy from=
 BMAD"</strong> Hard no. Every change still goes through your normal review=
 and release process.</p>
<p local-id=3D"050e459aa6fb">=E2=9D=8C <strong>"It's just a fancy chatbot"<=
/strong> It's a structured methodology. The agents have specific purposes, =
produce specific outputs, and follow a specific process. Treat them like a =
specialist, not Google.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f89a70626a77">=E2=9D=8C <strong>"Once I set it up, I never h=
ave to think again"</strong> After a long session, AI can start to lose the=
 plot a little =E2=80=94 responses feel off, context gets fuzzy. It's norma=
l. Just <strong>start a fresh session</strong> and you're golden. =E2=9C=A8=
</p>
